{
  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, relations between survival and mutations in TP53, high expression of BIRC5, and other types of genomic alterations were shown as well.",
    "Elmarakeby et al. [89] in 2021 discovered that alterations of formerly unrelated genes such as MDM4, FGFR1, or MALM3 are associated with prostate cancer outcomes.",
    "For this they used a neural network with specific constraints: nodes represent a biological entity and edges their relations.",
    "By doing so, they limited the degree of connectivity in the network to incorporate prior biological knowledge and to restrict the computational complexity.",
    "The advantage of genomics in prognosis predictions lies in the ability to obtain data at multiple levels, which can range from genomic properties to its specific sequences."
  ]
}